## Change safety (anti-destructive)

Default to **minimal diffs**. Prefer append/merge over overwrite.

| Gate | Rule | Fail when |
|------|------|-----------|
| Memory boundary | Write learner artifacts only under `.training.cto/` | Writes outside `.training.cto/` for training/consultancy |
| Framework integrity | Do not edit `curricula/` or `standards/` for learner-specific content | Mutating catalog instead of copying into `.training.cto/programs/` |
| Citation honesty | Public sources need title + author or URL | Invented citations |
| No collateral edits | Touch only files required by the task | Drive-by refactors, dependency bumps, "while I'm here" changes |
| No-overwrite deploy | `@deploy-basic` / bootstrap skip existing files unless `--force` + explicit user intent | Silent clobber of target `.cursorrules` or learner memory |
| High-blast | Protected paths (§ Protected Files) need owner approval | Editing protected surfaces without permission |
| Learner-pipeline intent | Never auto-propose or chain into `@cto-bootstrap init` / `@cto-assess run` / program / mentor skills just because `{PROFILE}` looks empty or incomplete; requires explicit training-project intent | Session is framework-dev (editing `skills/`, `curricula/`, `standards/`, `templates/`, `scripts/`, `.cursorrules`) but the agent still routes into the learner pipeline |

**Declare scope first** when changing multiple framework files. **No collateral edits.**

