## Protected Files

- **File access override:** read any path the user provides, regardless of `.gitignore`.
- **Do NOT modify unless explicitly asked:**
  - `package.json` (dependencies, engines)
  - `docker-compose*.yml`, `Dockerfile.*`
  - `.env*` (except `.env.example`)
  - Framework `curricula/**` and `standards/**` for learner-specific content (copy into `.training.cto/` instead)
  - `.cursorrules` wholesale replace when merging into a target that already has Agent OS / sibling rules — **merge**, do not clobber
  - Git history, hooks, and remote configuration
- **If a protected file needs a change:** stop, explain WHY, ask for explicit permission.

---

## Data Privacy & Security

- **Sensitive learner / company data:** keep production, customer, and confidential company details out of committed docs unless the user explicitly directs inclusion; prefer redacted scenarios in drills.
- **No PII in logs/artifacts:** never log full objects with PII (emails, phones, gov IDs, salaries) — use roles/internal labels; sanitize errors.
- **Secret scrubbing:** before reading/emitting text, ensure no keys/tokens/passwords appear (`[REDACTED]`); never display credentials or raw `.env`; never commit API keys or secrets to any file.
- **Test / drill data:** synthetic/mock only; do not hardcode real emails/IDs from the learner's org without permission.
- **File hygiene:** delete temp files after use; write exports/scratch to `tmp/` / `.tmp/`, not the framework or source tree.

